ween monarchy and colonialism, from the old regime empires down to the Commonwealth of today. With case studies drawn from Britain, France, the Netherlands, Germany and Italy, the chapters analyse constitutional questions about the role of the crown in overseas empires, the pomp and pageantry of the monarchy as it transferred to the colonies, and the fate of indigenous sovereigns under European colonial control. The volume, with chapters on North America, Asia, Africa and Australasia, provides new perspectives on colonial history, the governance of empire, and the transnational history of monarchies in modern Europe.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aImperialismxEuropexHistory. 0aImperialism. 0aKings and rulers. 0aMonarchyxHistoryxEurope. 0aMonarchyzEuropexHistory. 4aStudies in Imperialism 2017. 7aHISTORY / Europe / General.2bisacsh  aColonies.  aEmpire.  aEurope.  aMonarchy.  acrowns.1 aAldrich, Robert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAldrich, Robert, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBaskerville, Bruce, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFitzpatrick, Matthew P., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGelman Taylor, Jean, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGuenot, Emmanuelle, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKumarasingham, H., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMasselos, Jim, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcCreery, Cindy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcCreery, Cindy, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMcKenna, Mark, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary